title: Natalie Merchant - VH1 Storytellers [2005] DVD5
description: Natalie Merchant: VH1 Storytellers [2005] DVD5 Natalie Merchant got her start at age 17 as the lead singer of the folk-pop outfit 10,000 Maniacs. Her silken voice and outspoken social awareness wooed music fans and cemented her status as one of the day's most astute and captivating artists. Though 10,000 Maniacs achieved a level of critical success as a major-label act in the mid-80's, Merchant decided to go it alone in 1994. Since then her popularity has bloomed in the wake of Tigerlily, Ophelia, Motherland, Live in Concert: Natalie Merchant and The House Carpenter's Daughter. Featured here are the hits in an intimate, one-of-a-kind setting. Each song (except tracks 1 & 8) is preceded by an introduction by Natalie Merchant. The tracklist and the durations here above don't take into account those introductions. Total disc duration (including introductions and bonus tracks) is 55mn 06s. Audio offers the choice of either LPCM 2-ch or AC3 5.1-ch.
